00:09:37.450 --> 00:09:39.470
Hello, everyone.

00:09:39.470 --> 00:09:42.110
I am your 13th chairman, Pariston.

00:09:42.110 --> 00:09:45.020
And I have an important announcement.

00:09:46.350 --> 00:09:50.450
I, Pariston, name Cheadle-san as vice chairman,

00:09:50.450 --> 00:09:53.280
and resign as chairman.

00:09:55.460 --> 00:09:56.780
Okay, then.

00:09:58.100 --> 00:10:00.450
I didn't see that coming.

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:07.410
How long must you make fools of us?!

00:10:07.410 --> 00:10:08.670
Come back here!

00:10:12.750 --> 00:10:17.930
I didn't become vice chairman because
I wanted to become chairman.

00:10:18.690 --> 00:10:21.530
I just wanted to hinder the chairman.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:27.580
When I said silly things to tease him,

00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:30.190
Netero-san always looked so happy...

00:10:31.670 --> 00:10:35.450
I really wanted to play with him some more.

00:10:44.430 --> 00:10:47.960
I recommend that you reform the Hunter
Exam and Commandments quickly.

00:10:52.860 --> 00:10:58.340
Cheadle-san, if the Association becomes
a dull place under your leadership,

00:11:01.880 --> 00:11:04.510
I'll get serious about toying with you.

00:11:16.800 --> 00:11:18.830
Leorio, where's Killua?

00:11:18.830 --> 00:11:19.620
Huh?

00:11:19.620 --> 00:11:22.400
Oh, I don't know.

00:11:22.400 --> 00:11:24.270
He isn't answering his phone.

00:11:24.270 --> 00:11:28.720
It sounds like he was traveling,
looking for a way to save you.

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:32.250
Well, once we contact him,
I'm sure he'll come see you.

00:11:34.480 --> 00:11:37.440
I need to apologize to Killua.

00:11:38.030 --> 00:11:41.260
When I was fighting the enemy, I got confused,

00:11:41.260 --> 00:11:43.190
and I said terrible things to him.

00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:49.150
I'm sorry, too.

00:11:49.150 --> 00:11:50.020
Huh?

00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:52.300
Why are you apologizing?

00:11:53.490 --> 00:11:57.150
Well, sorry that I couldn't do anything
when you guys were in trouble.

00:11:57.330 --> 00:11:59.190
Huh? What do you mean?

00:11:59.190 --> 00:12:00.660
I don't get it.

00:12:01.180 --> 00:12:03.650
Yeah, I'm really sorry.

00:12:14.600 --> 00:12:16.920
The requests following a wish for a computer

00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:20.190
should be more severe than playing
dead and a pat on the head.

00:12:25.550 --> 00:12:30.130
When I heard Milluki's report,
that was the first thing that seemed off.

00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:34.780
And when the two-choice wish resulted
in a simple kiss on the cheek,

00:12:35.620 --> 00:12:39.510
it demanded fingernails, a far too heavy price.

00:12:40.830 --> 00:12:44.470
Assuming that the fingernails were
the price for the computer,

00:12:45.030 --> 00:12:51.170
Wish                                            Request

00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:50.540
that would match the balance between
wishes and requests seen previously.

00:12:51.910 --> 00:12:54.300
If my theory is correct,

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:59.140
playing dead and the pat on the head
weren't requests from Something.

00:12:59.140 --> 00:13:04.540
Thus, the two-choice wish didn't require a payment.

00:13:05.870 --> 00:13:07.870
Why was that the case?

00:13:08.720 --> 00:13:10.690
There are two possibilities.

00:13:11.790 --> 00:13:15.170
One, because the wish was simple enough

00:13:15.170 --> 00:13:17.350
that Something's power wasn't required.

00:13:18.810 --> 00:13:20.010
Two,

00:13:20.420 --> 00:13:22.260
because it wasn't a wish.

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:27.330
However, there's still an unresolved question here.

00:13:28.150 --> 00:13:32.200
If playing dead and the pat on the head
weren't requests from Something...

00:13:33.100 --> 00:13:37.600
They were requests from Alluka, not Something.

00:13:39.230 --> 00:13:43.080
Killua claims that Something calls him "Killua,"

00:13:43.550 --> 00:13:47.650
and the request to play dead was made to "Brother."

00:13:49.170 --> 00:13:53.920
Thus, the one who calls Killua "Brother" is Alluka.

00:13:55.210 --> 00:13:58.710
If the request came from Alluka,

00:13:58.710 --> 00:14:00.780
then Something wasn't awake,

00:14:00.780 --> 00:14:05.360
and Killua shouldn't have been
able to make the two-choice wish.

00:14:06.120 --> 00:14:09.950
However, Something responded to Killua's wish.

00:14:11.180 --> 00:14:14.690
The hint to resolving this contradiction
lies in the wording Killua used.

00:14:15.050 --> 00:14:17.950
When making the two-choice wish,
Killua was not asking.

00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:19.520
He was commanding.

00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:23.760
It makes sense that a command
would work differently than a wish,

00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:28.220
and would not require a payment upon completion.

00:14:30.110 --> 00:14:32.580
Those are my conclusions.

00:14:32.580 --> 00:14:33.770
What do you think?

00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:40.910
I'll get to the point.

00:14:41.440 --> 00:14:47.020
I'm the one who can use Something's power,
effectively and safely, for the Zoldyck family.

00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:52.670
As it stands, Alluka is no more than
a spirit locked forever in one room.

00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:56.920
But if I control him with you at his side,

00:14:59.840 --> 00:15:03.500
at the very least, I can guarantee his freedom.

00:15:05.510 --> 00:15:06.560
Brother...

00:15:18.400 --> 00:15:20.840
I'll protect Alluka.

00:15:21.990 --> 00:15:24.280
Kil, you need to learn your place.

00:15:25.230 --> 00:15:27.610
Something, wake up.

00:15:32.390 --> 00:15:33.270
'Kay.

00:15:40.600 --> 00:15:43.110
Kil, this is your last chance.

00:15:43.710 --> 00:15:45.130
Let me have Something—

00:15:45.130 --> 00:15:46.130
Something!

00:15:46.620 --> 00:15:49.130
Send Illumi back home!

00:15:49.870 --> 00:15:50.630
'Kay.

00:15:57.230 --> 00:15:58.990
Teleportation...

00:15:58.990 --> 00:16:00.270
For real?

00:16:01.040 --> 00:16:03.330
Oh, you were all watching?

00:16:05.940 --> 00:16:08.700
That's amazing... He's invincible.

00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.280
If Killua issues a command,

00:16:12.940 --> 00:16:15.010
there is no need to worry about requests.

00:16:16.600 --> 00:16:21.440
This means that turning Killua into
my puppet is worth any price.

00:16:23.020 --> 00:16:25.090
Tsubone, Amane...

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:28.440
Can you leave us alone for a moment?

00:16:29.580 --> 00:16:31.430
If you don't leave on your own,

00:16:31.880 --> 00:16:34.200
I'll have to issue Something a command.

00:16:35.730 --> 00:16:39.440
Killua, pat my head...

00:16:40.100 --> 00:16:43.850
Something is doing this because
she wants me to praise her.

00:16:44.690 --> 00:16:48.780
I don't want to use her by issuing commands.

00:16:52.470 --> 00:16:53.470
So please...

00:16:55.260 --> 00:16:56.820
Killua...

00:16:58.420 --> 00:17:00.210
Killua!

00:17:01.400 --> 00:17:02.830
Killua!

00:17:04.210 --> 00:17:05.940
Killua...

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:08.220
Something...

00:17:09.230 --> 00:17:12.990
Killua, pat my head.

00:17:14.350 --> 00:17:18.380
You can't come out anymore.

00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:27.270
I love Killua.

00:17:33.890 --> 00:17:35.280
You can't come out, Something.

00:17:36.250 --> 00:17:38.480
I love Killua.

00:17:39.340 --> 00:17:41.660
I love Killua!

00:17:41.970 --> 00:17:42.620
You can't!

00:17:43.090 --> 00:17:44.670
Never come out again!

00:17:44.670 --> 00:17:45.630
Got it?

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:54.050
'Kay...

00:18:04.580 --> 00:18:07.680
Alluka is free now.

00:18:11.230 --> 00:18:12.010
I'm sorry.

00:18:12.770 --> 00:18:14.250
I'm sorry, Something.

00:18:17.180 --> 00:18:18.120
I'm sorry...

00:18:24.440 --> 00:18:25.280
Alluka?

00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:37.430
Brother?

00:18:37.910 --> 00:18:39.850
Yep, it's your big—

00:18:41.480 --> 00:18:45.060
Did you make Something cry?

00:18:45.060 --> 00:18:45.960
Huh?

00:18:45.960 --> 00:18:48.820
Er, well...

00:18:49.790 --> 00:18:52.320
She's still hunched over, crying!

00:18:52.320 --> 00:18:54.270
Apologize to her!

00:18:55.240 --> 00:18:56.340
But...

00:18:56.340 --> 00:18:57.700
Apologize!

00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:03.220
If you're nice to me, you have to
be nice to Something, too!

00:19:12.510 --> 00:19:17.590
If you're going to protect me,
you have to protect Something, too!

00:19:21.120 --> 00:19:25.070
If you're mean to Something, I'll hate you!

00:19:33.280 --> 00:19:36.320
Alluka, thank you.

00:19:37.410 --> 00:19:41.280
I guess I was still under Ill-nii's control.

00:19:42.780 --> 00:19:45.810
But everything's okay now.

00:19:47.740 --> 00:19:50.500
Can you tell Something to come out?

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:08.650
Something, I'm sorry.

00:20:09.220 --> 00:20:10.660
I was wrong.

00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:12.240
I'm sorry!

00:20:13.100 --> 00:20:15.780
I was scared of Ill-nii,

00:20:15.780 --> 00:20:17.130
and I couldn't defy him.

00:20:17.130 --> 00:20:20.690
So I did what he said, and I hated it.

00:20:21.380 --> 00:20:24.710
When I realized he might force you

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:28.720
to do bad things, too, I got really scared...

00:20:30.750 --> 00:20:33.290
For Alluka's sake, I lied to myself,

00:20:34.200 --> 00:20:35.800
and I said mean things to you.

00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:39.350
I'm really sorry!

00:20:42.300 --> 00:20:43.180
Something,

00:20:44.030 --> 00:20:45.900
I'll protect you.

00:20:45.900 --> 00:20:47.260
We'll always be together!

00:20:47.910 --> 00:20:50.330
Don't listen to wishes from anyone else anymore!

00:20:50.330 --> 00:20:53.010
I'll pat you on the head whenever you want!

00:20:54.210 --> 00:20:59.390
So would you please come out again?

00:21:12.190 --> 00:21:13.210
'Kay...

00:21:20.380 --> 00:21:21.220
Something,

00:21:22.520 --> 00:21:25.830
will you forgive me for being a

00:21:27.760 --> 00:21:29.100
bad big brother?

00:21:31.030 --> 00:21:32.010
'Kay.

00:21:38.820 --> 00:21:39.990
I...

00:21:43.020 --> 00:21:44.240
love Killua.

00:21:46.650 --> 00:21:51.000
Tsubone, I've rescinded the restriction on Killua.

00:21:51.500 --> 00:21:53.790
Please let him know.

00:21:54.600 --> 00:21:58.600
Yes, I understand.

00:23:21.330 --> 00:23:23.170
His first friend.

00:23:23.170 --> 00:23:25.050
Too many memories to speak of.

00:23:25.050 --> 00:23:27.640
A new journey.

00:23:28.180 --> 00:23:30.760
